Gemini said






*Mapping the Way: Visual Routing is Finally Here!*







Managing bulk orders just got a major visual upgrade. We are thrilled to
introduce *Map-Based Routing*, a brand-new way to group and allocate your
unrouted orders directly from an interactive map interface. No more
guessing geometries or squinting at tabular lists=E2=80=94just clear visibi=
lity and
smarter ad-hoc dispatching.


Why We Built This?












While our auto-allocation logic handles various scenarios seamlessly, some
businesses require manual routing due to very specific on-ground SOPs.


You can find map view in :
*Orders*
*=E2=86=92 Pidge Powered =E2=86=92 Map View (top right corner)(With a singl=
e click, switch
from a grid list to a dynamic geographic view)*
What=E2=80=99s New!


*Forward Orders/Reverse Orders*

Pinpoints single-hub pickup locations alongside multiple drop destinations,
featuring a left-hand summary panel of order counts per hub and a
quick-reset map button for both forward and reverse orders.

*This view shows all pickup points for unprocessed forward orders.*

*This view displays all associated drop locations (for all orders) after
you click on a selected pickup point icon.*




*Hover Insights*

Hovering over any map pin instantly highlights essential delivery metrics,
including delivery/pickup dates, promised windows, and operational wait
times.

*Once the user hover over a pin, all the details pertaining to that order
are visible*





*On-the-Fly Route Construction*

Add orders to a route sequentially with a built-in Call-to-Action. Watch
your delivery sequence connect in real-time with visual routing lines,
rearrange legs dynamically, and assign everything to a *Captive Rider*
 seamlessly.

*User can map out delivery route choosing where the sequence of deliveries*


What This Means To You






   1.

   *Zero Visibility Gaps:* You can now see your delivery clusters and
   bundle nearby orders efficiently as per custom SOPs


   2.

   *Ad-Hoc Efficiency:* Spot an active rider near a fresh pickup location?
   Allocate orders on the fly without bouncing back and forth into the live
   tracking dashboard. Reduce rider transit distances, cut fuel costs, and
   drastically accelerate your delivery turnarounds.

What=E2=80=99s Next

Something exciting is coming soon - Stay tuned !!
